<Layouts.app flash={@flash} current_scope={@current_scope}>
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
    <div class="mb-10">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-foreground sm:text-4xl">
        Terms of Service
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-muted-foreground">Last updated: April 10, 2026</p>
    </div>

    <div class="prose prose-sm dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
      <p class="text-base leading-7 text-muted-foreground">
        Please read these Terms of Service ("Terms") carefully before using the AgentEx platform (the "Service"). By accessing or using the Service, you agree to be bound by these Terms. If you disagree with any part of the Terms, you may not access the Service.
      </p>

      <h2 class="mt-10 text-xl font-semibold text-foreground">1. Definitions</h2>
      <ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-5 text-muted-foreground">
        <li>
          <strong>"Service"</strong>
          refers to the AgentEx platform, including all features, AI agent orchestration, chat interfaces, and integrations.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>"User"</strong>
          refers to any individual who registers for or accesses the Service.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>"Organization"</strong>
          refers to a workspace within the Service that can contain multiple users, agents, and resources.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>"AI Agents"</strong>
          refers to configured AI models and their behaviors within the platform.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>"Content"</strong>
          refers to text, prompts, messages, configurations, and other data created or uploaded by users.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="mt-10 text-xl font-semibold text-foreground">2. Account Registration</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-base leading-7 text-muted-foreground">
        To use the Service, you must create an account. You may register using an email and password or through a third-party authentication provider (e.g., Google OAuth). You are responsible for:
      </p>
      <ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-5 text-muted-foreground">
        <li>Maintaining the confidentiality of your account credentials</li>
        <li>All activities that occur under your account</li>
        <li>Notifying us immediately of any unauthorized access</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="mt-10 text-xl font-semibold text-foreground">3. Acceptable Use</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-base leading-7 text-muted-foreground">
        You agree not to use the Service to:
      </p>
      <ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-5 text-muted-foreground">
        <li>Violate any applicable laws or regulations</li>
        <li>Transmit harmful, fraudulent, or malicious content</li>
        <li>Impersonate another person or entity</li>
        <li>Attempt to gain unauthorized access to the Service or its systems</li>
        <li>Interfere with or disrupt the integrity or performance of the Service</li>
        <li>Create agents or tools designed to cause harm or spread malware</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="mt-10 text-xl font-semibold text-foreground">4. AI Agents and Tools</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-base leading-7 text-muted-foreground">
        The Service allows you to create, configure, and interact with AI agents. You acknowledge that:
      </p>
      <ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-5 text-muted-foreground">
        <li>AI-generated content may contain inaccuracies and should be reviewed before use</li>
        <li>You are responsible for the actions and outputs of agents you create</li>
        <li>
          Tool execution (including web fetching, shell commands, and custom HTTP tools) may produce unintended results
        </li>
        <li>
          You should exercise caution when granting agents access to external systems or sensitive data
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="mt-10 text-xl font-semibold text-foreground">5. Third-Party AI Providers</h2>
      <div class="my-6 rounded-xl border border-amber-200 bg-amber-50 p-5 dark:border-amber-800/50 dark:bg-amber-950/30">
        <div class="flex gap-3">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0">
            <svg
              class="size-6 text-amber-500"
              fill="none"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              stroke-width="1.5"
              stroke="currentColor"
            >
              <path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                d="M12 9v3.75m-9.303 3.376c-.866 1.5.217 3.374 1.948 3.374h14.71c1.73 0 2.813-1.874 1.948-3.374L13.949 3.378c-.866-1.5-3.032-1.5-3.898 0L2.697 16.126ZM12 15.75h.007v.008H12v-.008Z"
              />
            </svg>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-amber-800 dark:text-amber-200">
              Important: Third-Party AI Services
            </h3>
            <div class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-amber-700 dark:text-amber-300">
              <p>
                The Service integrates with third-party artificial intelligence providers, including but not limited to:
              </p>
              <ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-5">
                <li><strong>OpenAI</strong> (GPT-4, GPT-4o, o-series models)</li>
                <li><strong>Google</strong> (Gemini models)</li>
                <li>Other large language model providers accessible through the platform</li>
              </ul>
              <p class="mt-3">
                When you interact with AI agents, your prompts, conversation history, and related data are transmitted to and processed by these third-party providers. Each provider operates under its own terms of service and privacy policy, which govern how your data is collected, processed, stored, and used.
              </p>
              <p class="mt-3">
                <strong>We do not control these third-party services</strong>
                and are not responsible for their practices, content, or availability. We encourage you to review the terms and privacy policies of any AI provider you use through our platform.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="mt-4 text-base leading-7 text-muted-foreground">
        By using AI agents through our Service, you acknowledge and agree that:
      </p>
      <ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-5 text-muted-foreground">
        <li>Your data will be transmitted to third-party AI providers for processing</li>
        <li>These providers may retain your data in accordance with their own policies</li>
        <li>
          The quality, accuracy, and appropriateness of AI-generated responses depend on the underlying provider's models
        </li>
        <li>
          Availability of AI services is subject to the third-party provider's uptime and terms
        </li>
        <li>
          Usage limits, pricing, and availability of specific models are determined by the respective providers
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="mt-10 text-xl font-semibold text-foreground">6. Telegram Integration</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-base leading-7 text-muted-foreground">
        The Service offers integration with Telegram messenger. When you use this feature:
      </p>
      <ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-5 text-muted-foreground">
        <li>Messages sent and received through Telegram are processed by our gateway system</li>
        <li>These messages are also visible within the web-based chat interface</li>
        <li>You are responsible for complying with Telegram's Terms of Service</li>
        <li>Telegram's privacy policy applies to messages transmitted through their platform</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="mt-10 text-xl font-semibold text-foreground">7. Intellectual Property</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-base leading-7 text-muted-foreground">
        The Service and its original content, features, and functionality are owned by AgentEx and are protected by applicable intellectual property laws. You retain ownership of Content you create, but grant us a license to use, store, and display it as necessary to provide the Service.
      </p>

      <h2 class="mt-10 text-xl font-semibold text-foreground">
        8. Organizations and Collaboration
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-base leading-7 text-muted-foreground">
        Users can create and join organizations. Within an organization:
      </p>
      <ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-5 text-muted-foreground">
        <li>
          Organization administrators have visibility and control over agents, tools, and chat rooms
        </li>
        <li>
          Resources created within an organization may be accessible to other members based on roles
        </li>
        <li>
          Leaving or being removed from an organization may result in loss of access to organization-scoped resources
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="mt-10 text-xl font-semibold text-foreground">9. Disclaimer of Warranties</h2>
      <div class="my-4 rounded-lg border border-border bg-muted/30 p-4 text-sm text-muted-foreground">
        THE SERVICE IS PROVIDED ON AN "AS IS" AND "AS AVAILABLE" BASIS, WITHOUT WARRANTIES OF ANY KIND, WHETHER EXPRESS, IMPLIED, OR STATUTORY, INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO WARRANTIES OF MERCHANTABILITY, FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE, AND NON-INFRINGEMENT.
      </div>
      <p class="mt-2 text-base leading-7 text-muted-foreground">
        We do not warrant that:
      </p>
      <ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-5 text-muted-foreground">
        <li>The Service will be uninterrupted, secure, or error-free</li>
        <li>AI-generated responses will be accurate, complete, or reliable</li>
        <li>Third-party AI providers will be available or perform to your expectations</li>
        <li>Any defects in the Service will be corrected</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="mt-10 text-xl font-semibold text-foreground">10. Limitation of Liability</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-base leading-7 text-muted-foreground">
        TO THE MAXIMUM EXTENT PERMITTED BY LAW, AGENTEX SHALL NOT BE LIABLE FOR ANY INDIRECT, INCIDENTAL, SPECIAL, CONSEQUENTIAL, OR PUNITIVE DAMAGES, INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO LOSS OF PROFITS, DATA, USE, OR OTHER INTANGIBLE LOSSES, RESULTING FROM:
      </p>
      <ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-5 text-muted-foreground">
        <li>Your use or inability to use the Service</li>
        <li>
          Actions or outputs of AI agents, including inaccurate or harmful generated content
        </li>
        <li>Unauthorized access to or alteration of your transmissions or data</li>
        <li>Statements or conduct of any third party (including AI providers) on the Service</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="mt-10 text-xl font-semibold text-foreground">11. Indemnification</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-base leading-7 text-muted-foreground">
        You agree to indemnify and hold harmless AgentEx and its officers, directors, employees, and agents from any claims, liabilities, damages, losses, and expenses (including reasonable attorneys' fees) arising out of or related to your use of the Service, your Content, or your violation of these Terms.
      </p>

      <h2 class="mt-10 text-xl font-semibold text-foreground">12. Termination</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-base leading-7 text-muted-foreground">
        We may terminate or suspend your access to the Service immediately, without prior notice or liability, for any reason whatsoever, including without limitation if you breach these Terms. Upon termination, your right to use the Service will cease immediately.
      </p>

      <h2 class="mt-10 text-xl font-semibold text-foreground">13. Changes to Terms</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-base leading-7 text-muted-foreground">
        We reserve the right to modify these Terms at any time. We will provide notice of material changes by posting the updated Terms on this page with a new "Last updated" date. Your continued use of the Service after such modifications constitutes your acceptance of the revised Terms.
      </p>

      <h2 class="mt-10 text-xl font-semibold text-foreground">14. Governing Law</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-base leading-7 text-muted-foreground">
        These Terms shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of the jurisdiction in which AgentEx operates, without regard to its conflict of law provisions.
      </p>

      <h2 class="mt-10 text-xl font-semibold text-foreground">15. Contact</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-base leading-7 text-muted-foreground">
        If you have any questions about these Terms, please contact us at <strong class="text-foreground">contact&#64;sukacipta.com</strong>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layouts.app>
